<caption id="DF1C6612FF9DFFF2FF6FFBD5FCAF25E4" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" startId="40.[145,225,1122,1144]" targetBox="[305,1265,195,1082]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF9DFFF2FF6FFBD5FCAF25E4" blockId="40.[145,1425,1122,1173]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FF6FFBD5FEAE2506" bold="true" box="[145,265,1122,1144]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Figure 29.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FEEBFBD4FE582509" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1912" box="[277,511,1122,1144]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paraprotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atroluteus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FEEBFBD4FE582509" box="[277,511,1122,1144]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Paraprotus atroluteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, syntype (SMF RI 291). A, dDorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. D, original label. Scale bars: 1 mm. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF9DFFF2FF6FFB0BFE2A243A" blockId="40.[145,761,1211,1356]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FF6FFB0BFEAE25A0" box="[145,265,1212,1233]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FE35FB0BFDF825A1" authorityName="ROEWERR" authorityYear="1947" box="[459,607,1211,1233]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paraprotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albithorax">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FE35FB0BFDF825A1" box="[459,607,1211,1233]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">P. albithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having in carapace the same colour of abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9DFFF2FDC5FB6DFD3F259E" box="[571,664,1242,1264]" captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="40.[145,225,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,195,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-319@40.[305,1265,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 29. Paraprotus atroluteus, syntype (SMF RI 291). A, dDorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. D, original label. Scale bars: 1 mm. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Fig. 29A</figureCitation>
) instead of yellow spots. Abdomen with slightly yellowish coloration in lateral margins (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9DFFF2FE18FAA0FDE3245D" box="[486,580,1303,1325]" captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="40.[145,225,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,195,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-319@40.[305,1265,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 29. Paraprotus atroluteus, syntype (SMF RI 291). A, dDorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. D, original label. Scale bars: 1 mm. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Fig. 29A</figureCitation>
). Tarsal counts: 7(3), 17(3)/19(3), 9, 10.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF9DFFF2FF6FFAC8FD1D24A3" blockId="40.[145,760,1407,1491]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FF6FFAC8FE8824E5" box="[145,303,1407,1428]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Distribution:</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="54D88838FF9DFFF2FDA5FA37FD2824E4" box="[603,655,1408,1429]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">type</typeStatus>
locality. Eastern Cordillera real montane forest ecoregion in 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F878FF9DFFF2FF6FFA0AFE6A24A2" box="[145,461,1469,1491]" country="Ecuador" name="Zamora-Chinchipe" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Zamora Chinchipe Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFF9DFFF2FE11FA0AFDE924A2" box="[495,590,1469,1491]" name="Ecuador" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9DFFF2FDA3FA0AFD0D24A3" box="[605,682,1469,1491]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="35.[163,241,1281,1303]" captionTargetBox="[325,1281,197,1240]" captionTargetId="figure-292@35.[323,1283,195,1241]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 23. Map of known distribution of Paraprotus and Kayania. Numbers correspond to the following WWF ecoregions: 1 = Eastern Cordillera real montane forest, 2 = Ucayali moist forest, 3 = Peruvian yungas." pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF9DFFF2FF6FF9B1FD83263E" blockId="40.[145,761,1542,1871]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FF6FF9B1FF5C276A" box="[145,251,1542,1563]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Remarks:</emphasis>
Although it was described from ‘Columbien (
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FF67F992FEAA274A" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[153,269,1573,1595]" class="Arachnida" family="Agoristenidae" genus="Sabanilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sabanilla</taxonomicName>
)’ (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9DFFF2FED2F992FE36274B" box="[300,401,1573,1595]" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="39.[163,243,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,915,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-300@39.[323,1283,915,1794]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 28. Paraprotus albithorax, female holotype (SMF RII 132/2). A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. D, original label. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Fig. 28D</figureCitation>
), the correct place is possibly 
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFF9DFFF2FF6FF9F4FEBB2729" box="[145,284,1603,1624]" name="Ecuador" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">ECUADOR</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F878FF9DFFF2FED5F9F4FDB42728" box="[299,531,1603,1625]" country="Ecuador" name="Zamora-Chinchipe" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Zamora-Chinchipe</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FDDDF9F4FD3A2728" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[547,669,1603,1625]" class="Arachnida" family="Agoristenidae" genus="Sabanilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sabanilla</taxonomicName>
. In the description of various species, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFF9DFFF2FDFAF9D5FD0F2706" author="Roewer CF" box="[516,680,1634,1655]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" pagination="257 - 472" refId="ref54345" refString="Roewer CF. 1913. Die Familie der Gonyleptiden de Opiliones - Laniatores. [part 2]. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Abt. A, Original-Arbeiten 79: 257 - 472, pl. 2." type="journal article" year="1913">Roewer (1913</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFF9DFFF2FD49F9D5FD572706" author="Roewer CF" box="[695,752,1634,1655]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" refId="ref54471" refString="Roewer CF. 1923. Die Weberknechte der Erde. Systematische Bearbeitung der bisher bekannten Opiliones. Jena: Gustav Fischer." type="book" year="1923">1923</bibRefCitation>
) inconsistently cited 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FE6CF936FDAB27E7" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[402,524,1665,1686]" class="Arachnida" family="Agoristenidae" genus="Sabanilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FE6CF936FDAB27E7" box="[402,524,1665,1686]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Sabanilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
either as being in ‘Kolumbien’ or in ‘Venezuela’. 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FE0EF928FDC627C4" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[496,609,1695,1717]" class="Arachnida" family="Agoristenidae" genus="Sabanilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sabanilla</taxonomicName>
, in this case, probably refers to a small village called 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FD7BF909FD5F27A5" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[645,760,1726,1748]" class="Arachnida" family="Agoristenidae" genus="Sabanilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sabanilla</taxonomicName>
[–4.03333°, –79.01667°, 
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FE4BF96AFE672783" box="[437,448,1757,1778]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">c</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="4C9B9B7FFF9DFFF2FE2EF96BFD8B2783" box="[464,556,1756,1778]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
], on the old road between 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F878FF9DFFF2FEF6F94CFE982660" box="[264,319,1787,1809]" country="Ecuador" name="Loja" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Loja</collectingRegion>
and Zamora (
<collectingRegion id="49A7F878FF9DFFF2FDFEF94CFD552660" box="[512,754,1787,1809]" country="Ecuador" name="Zamora-Chinchipe" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Zamora-Chinchipe</collectingRegion>
, southern Ecuador). A subsequent record (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFF9DFFF2FD64F8ADFF6F263F" author="Roewer CF" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" pagination="527 - 632" refId="ref54532" refString="Roewer CF. 1928 [' 1927 ']. Weitere Weberknechte II. (2. Erganzung der Weberknechte der Erde, 1923). Abhandlungen der Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 26: 527 - 632." type="journal article" year="1928">Roewer, 1928</bibRefCitation>
) reinforces our interpretation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF9DFFF2FCBFFB0CFAE82772" blockId="40.[809,1426,1211,1540]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">
Although external similarity is encountered comparing the 
<typeStatus id="54D88838FF9DFFF2FC17FB6DFBB9259E" box="[1001,1054,1242,1263]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">type</typeStatus>
specimens of both species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FCD7FB4EFC0C247F" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1912" box="[809,939,1273,1294]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paraprotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FCD7FB4EFC0C247F" box="[809,939,1273,1294]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Paraprotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9DFFF2FC45FB4EFBB6247F" box="[955,1041,1273,1295]" captionStart="Figure 29" captionStartId="40.[145,225,1122,1144]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,195,1082]" captionTargetId="figure-319@40.[305,1265,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 29. Paraprotus atroluteus, syntype (SMF RI 291). A, dDorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. D, original label. Scale bars: 1 mm. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Figs 29</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9DFFF2FBDEFB4EFB9B247F" box="[1056,1084,1273,1294]" captionStart="Figure 30" captionStartId="41.[163,241,928,950]" captionTargetBox="[165,1446,197,888]" captionTargetId="figure-513@41.[163,1446,195,889]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 30. Map of known distribution of Protus. Numbers correspond to the following WWF ecoregions: 1 = Ucayali moist forest, 2 = Iquitos varzea, 3 = Southwest Amazon moist forest, 4 = Solimões-Japurá moist forest, 5 = Juruá-Purus moist forest, 6 = Madeira-Tapajos moist forest, 7 = Japurá-Solimões-Negro moist forest, 8 = Uatuma-Trombetas moist forest, 9 = Mato Grosso seasonal forest." pageId="40" pageNumber="625">30</figureCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFF9DFFF2FBADFB4EFA94247E" author="Roewer CF" box="[1107,1331,1273,1295]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref54310" refString="Roewer CF. 1912. Die Familie der Cosmetiden Opiliones- Laniatores. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Abt. A, Original- Arbeiten 78: 1 - 122, + Taf. 1 - 2." type="journal article" year="1912">Roewer (1912: 120)</bibRefCitation>
made a detailed description of the coloration of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FB07FAAFFA2C245D" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1912" box="[1273,1419,1303,1325]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paraprotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atroluteus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FB07FAAFFA2C245D" box="[1273,1419,1303,1325]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">P. atroluteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, remarking that dorsal scutum was mostly light rustyellow except for brown-black coloration of ocularium and ventral surface (coxae and free sternites). Then, no yellow mark is described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFF9DFFF2FB4BFA25FAC224D9" author="Roewer CF" box="[1205,1381,1426,1448]" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref54310" refString="Roewer CF. 1912. Die Familie der Cosmetiden Opiliones- Laniatores. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Abt. A, Original- Arbeiten 78: 1 - 122, + Taf. 1 - 2." type="journal article" year="1912">Roewer (1912)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FCD7FA06FC1B24B7" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1912" box="[809,956,1457,1478]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paraprotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atroluteus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FCD7FA06FC1B24B7" box="[809,956,1457,1478]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">P. atroluteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a remarkable feature present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9DFFF2FCB6FA67FC7C2495" authorityName="ROEWERR" authorityYear="1947" box="[840,987,1487,1509]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paraprotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albithorax">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9DFFF2FCB6FA67FC7C2495" box="[840,987,1487,1509]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="625">P. albithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFF9DFFF2FAC4FA67FC352772" author="Roewer CF" pageId="40" pageNumber="625" pagination="7 - 57" refId="ref54632" refString="Roewer CF. 1947. Diagnosen neuer Gattungen und Arten der Opiliones Laniatores (Arachn.) aus C. F. Roewer's Sammlung im Senckenberg-Museum. 1. Cosmetidae. [Weitere Weberknechte XII]. Senckenbergiana 28: 7 - 57, pls 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1947">Roewer (1947: 33</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 12, fig. 106) and visible in 
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9DFFF2FB14FA59FAE82772" box="[1258,1359,1518,1540]" captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="39.[163,243,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,915,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-300@39.[323,1283,915,1794]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 28. Paraprotus albithorax, female holotype (SMF RII 132/2). A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. D, original label. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez." pageId="40" pageNumber="625">Fig. 28A.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
